{"defs":{"0":[{"path":["description"],"schema_type":"string"},{"path":["enabled"],"required":true,"schema_type":"boolean"},{"path":["unit"],"schema_type":"string"}],"1":[{"path":["date"]},{"path":["interval"]},{"path":["timestamp"]}],"2":[{"path":["_then"],"sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"],"keyword":"then"},{"path":["_then","coordRefSys"]},{"path":["_then","featureSchema"]},{"path":["_then","featureType"]},{"path":["_then","geometry"],"required":true},{"path":["_then","id"],"required":true,"schema_type":"string","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","measures"],"ref":"0"},{"path":["_then","place"]},{"path":["_then","properties"],"required":true,"schema_type":"object","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","properties","downholeDrillingDetails"],"description":"The property downholeDrillingDetails:DrillingDetails specifies the drilling method and borehole diameter for intervals down the borehole.","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","properties","downholeDrillingDetails","boreholeDiameter"],"description":"The boreholeDiameter property (SWE::Quantity) contains a measurement (a value and a unit of measure) corresponding to the diameter of the drilled hole.","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","properties","downholeDrillingDetails","drillingMethod"],"description":"The drillingMethod:BoreholeDrillingMethodCode property contains a term from a controlled vocabulary indicating the drilling method used. Appropriate terms would include rotary air blast, auger, diamond core, air core, etc.","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","properties","downholeDrillingDetails","intervalBegin"],"description":"The intervalBegin property (SWE::Quantity) contains a measurement (a value and a unit of measurement) that corresponds to the measured distance of the start of the interval along the path of the borehole. The measured value must be less than or equal to the intervalEnd value.","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","properties","downholeDrillingDetails","intervalEnd"],"description":"The property intervalEnd (SWE::Quantity) contains a measurement (a value and a unit of measurement) of the measured distance of the end of the interval along the path of the borehole. The measured value must be greater than or equal to the intervalBegin value.","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData"],"description":"The property indexData:BoreholeDetails describes metadata about a borehole, such as the operator, the custodian, dates of drilling, etc.","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData","boreholeLength"],"description":"The property boreholeLength (SWE::Quantity) contains a measurement (a value and a unit of measurement) corresponding to the \"length\" of a borehole determined by the data provider (i.e., \"length\" can have different sources, like drillers measurement, loggers measurement, survey measurement, etc.).","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData","boreholeMaterialCustodian"],"description":"The property boreholeMaterialCustodian is an association between BoreholeDetails and a CIT:CI_ResponsibleParty describing the organisation that is custodian of the drilled material recovered from the borehole.","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData","dataCustodian"],"description":"The dataCustodian is an association between a BoreholeDetails and a CIT:CI_ResponsibleParty describing the custodian (person or organisation) that is the custodian of data pertaining to this borehole.","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData","dateOfDrilling"],"description":"The property dateOfDrilling:TM_Period describes the time period during which drilling of the borehole occurred.","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData","driller"],"description":"The driller property is an association between a BoreholeDetails and a CIT:CI_ResponsibleParty describing of the organisation responsible for drilling the borehole (as opposed to commissioning the borehole).","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData","inclinationType"],"description":"The property inclinationType:BoreholeInclinationCode contains a term from a controlled vocabulary indicating the inclination type of the borehole. Appropriate terms would include vertical; inclined up; inclined down, horizontal.","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData","operator"],"description":"The operator property is an association between a BoreholeDetails and a CIT:CI_ResponsibleParty describing the organisation responsible for commissioning the borehole (as opposed to actually drilling the borehole).","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData","operator","schema:contributor"],"required":true},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData","operator","schema:contributor","schema:affiliation"],"description":"if affiliation is present, value must be a schema:Organization."},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData","operator","schema:contributor","schema:affiliation","schema:additionalType"],"schema_type":"array"},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData","operator","schema:contributor","schema:affiliation","schema:alternateName"],"description":"other labels by which the organization might be known","schema_type":"string"},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData","operator","schema:contributor","schema:affiliation","schema:description"],"schema_type":"string"},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData","operator","schema:contributor","schema:affiliation","schema:identifier"],"description":"identifier for organization"},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData","operator","schema:contributor","schema:affiliation","schema:name"],"description":"string label for organization that is meaningful for human users","schema_type":"string"},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData","operator","schema:contributor","schema:affiliation","schema:sameAs"],"description":"other identifiers for the organization","schema_type":"array"},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData","operator","schema:contributor","schema:alternateName"],"description":"other labels by which the person might be known","schema_type":"string"},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData","operator","schema:contributor","schema:contactPoint"],"description":"restrict to email only. Schema.org allows telephone and postal contacts as well","schema_type":"object"},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData","operator","schema:contributor","schema:contactPoint","schema:email"],"required":true,"schema_type":"string"},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData","operator","schema:contributor","schema:description"],"schema_type":"string"},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData","operator","schema:contributor","schema:identifier"],"description":"identifier for person, recommend ORCID"},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData","operator","schema:contributor","schema:name"],"description":"string label for person that is meaningful for human users, should format consistently. Recommend 'Family Name, Given name' format.","schema_type":"string"},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData","operator","schema:contributor","schema:sameAs"],"description":"other identifiers for the person","schema_type":"array"},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData","operator","schema:roleName"],"required":true},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData","purpose"],"description":"The property purpose:BoreholePurposeCode contains a term from a controlled vocabulary describing the purpose for which the borehole was drilled. e.g., site investigation, mineral exploration, hydrocarbon exploration, water resources.","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","properties","indexData","startPoint"],"description":"The property startPoint:BoreholeStartPointCode provides a term from a controlled vocabulary indicating the named position relative to ground surface where the borehole commenced. (e.g., natural ground surface, open pit floor, underground, offshore)","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","properties","logElement"],"description":"The property logElement is an association between a Borehole and a BoreholeInterval instance to describe measured downhole intervals and their observed features.","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","properties","referenceLocation"],"description":"The property referenceLocation is an association between a Borehole and an OriginPosition corresponding to the start point of a borehole log. This may correspond to the borehole collar location (e.g., kelly bush).","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","properties","referenceLocation","id"],"required":true,"schema_type":"string","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","properties","referenceLocation","properties"],"schema_type":"object","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","properties","referenceLocation","properties","elevation"],"description":"The elevation:DirectPosition property is a compromise approach to supply elevation explicitly for location; this is to allow for software that cannot process 3-D GM_Point. Null shall be used if elevation is unknown. A DirectPosition shall have a dimension of 1, and CRS will be a \"vertical\" CRS (e.g. EPSG CRSs in the range 5600-5799).","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","properties","referenceLocation","properties","location"],"description":"The property location contains a geometry corresponding to the location of the borehole collar.","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","properties","referenceLocation","properties","location","bbox"],"schema_type":"array"},{"path":["_then","properties","referenceLocation","properties","location","coordinates"],"required":true,"schema_type":"array"},{"path":["_then","properties","referenceLocation","properties","location","type"],"required":true,"schema_type":"string","enum":["Point"]},{"path":["_then","properties","referenceLocation","properties","relatedBorehole"],"description":"The hole that has this collar for its start point","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","time"],"ref":"1"},{"path":["_then","type"],"required":true,"const":"Feature"},{"path":["coordRefSys"]},{"path":["featureSchema"]},{"path":["featureType"]},{"path":["geometry"],"required":true},{"path":["id"]},{"path":["measures"],"ref":"0"},{"path":["place"]},{"path":["properties"],"required":true},{"path":["time"],"ref":"1"},{"path":["type"],"required":true,"const":"Feature"}]},"properties":[{"path":["_then"],"sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"],"keyword":"then"},{"path":["_then","type"],"required":true,"const":"FeatureCollection"},{"path":["_then","featureType"]},{"path":["_then","geometryDimension"],"schema_type":"integer"},{"path":["_then","featureSchema"]},{"path":["_then","coordRefSys"]},{"path":["_then","measures"],"ref":"0"},{"path":["_then","features"],"required":true,"schema_type":"array","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"],"ref":"2"},{"path":["_else"],"sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"],"keyword":"else","ref":"2"},{"path":["_then","features","_then","properties","logElement","_oneOf","1","_oneOf","1","properties","shape","_oneOf","5"],"title":"GeoJSON MultiPolygon","keyword":"branch"},{"path":["_then","features","_then","properties