properties","logElement","_oneOf","1","properties"],"schema_type":"object","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","features","_then","properties","logElement","_oneOf","1","properties","parentBorehole"],"description":"The property parentBorehole is an association between a BoreholeInterval and a Borehole to which the interval belongs.","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","features","_then","properties","logElement","_oneOf","1","properties","shape"],"description":"The property shape:GM_Object is a 1-D interval (e.g., a \"from\" and \"to\", or \"top\" and \"base\" measurement) covering the same distance as mappedIntervalBegin and mappedIntervalEnd. The geometry shall use a reference to the borehole as the CRS of the containing borehole.","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","features","_then","properties","logElement","_oneOf","1","properties","shape","bbox"],"schema_type":"array"},{"path":["_then","features","_then","properties","logElement","_oneOf","1","properties","shape","coordinates"],"required":true,"schema_type":"array"},{"path":["_then","features","_then","properties","logElement","_oneOf","1","properties","collectionIdentifier"],"description":"The collectionIdentifier:ScopedName is a string unique within a scope that identifies a collection which forms a set BoreholeIntervals. This allows description of multiple downhole logs for a single borehole. The name should identify a particular log observation event.","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"]},{"path":["_then","features","_then","properties","logElement","_oneOf","1","properties","collectionIdentifier","_anyOf"],"sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"],"keyword":"anyOf"},{"path":["_then","features","_then","properties","logElement","_oneOf","1","properties","collectionIdentifier","_anyOf","1"],"title":"a","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmBorehole"],"keyword":"branch"},